    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Jewish Tipping Point</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Maxine Skopov letter responds to Samuel G Freedman's August 13 article on dispute among Jews in Beachwood, Ohio (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>As a Conservative Jew, I believe that there are as many degrees of Jewish observance as there are Jews, and I applaud and celebrate the path that each takes. But shame on the Orthodox busybody who criticized Si Wachsberger for tending his property on Shabbos. And double shame on Wachsberger and his supporters who feel threatened by a large Orthodox community in their midst.</p>
        <p>Maxine Skopov  Orangeburg, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
